1
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:55,000
"Lost To You"

2
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,700
(Episode 5)

3
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:02,799
Some secrets tear people apart.

4
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:06,399
Some secrets bring people closer.

5
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:11,000
But our secret... brings
light to the darkness.

6
00:01:20,250 --> 00:01:20,833
Xiao Yuan.

7
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:21,833
Getting two servings today?

8
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Can you eat all that?

9
00:01:23,916 --> 00:01:26,208
He's definitely getting it for Zhan Wang.

10
00:01:26,666 --> 00:01:28,375
Zhan Wang gave him so many things.

11
00:01:28,708 --> 00:01:30,392
He has to at least get
him breakfast in return.

12
00:01:30,416 --> 00:01:30,958
No.

13
00:01:31,250 --> 00:01:32,625
I've just been eating more lately.

14
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Oh, come on.

15
00:01:34,083 --> 00:01:35,958
Mom said your appetite
hasn't changed at all.

16
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:37,833
It says in novels...

17
00:01:38,375 --> 00:01:40,916
When you worry if someone is hungry,

18
00:01:41,208 --> 00:01:42,208
if they're cold,

19
00:01:42,250 --> 00:01:43,750
or if they're unhappy...

20
00:01:44,291 --> 00:01:46,291
it means you've fallen for them.

21
00:01:46,375 --> 00:01:46,875
Xu Nuo.

22
00:01:47,333 --> 00:01:49,041
You should read less of that nonsense.

23
00:01:51,250 --> 00:01:52,541
Aren't you getting two?

24
00:01:52,791 --> 00:01:53,875
Take this one, too.

25
00:01:58,958 --> 00:01:59,958
So stubborn.

26
00:02:20,166 --> 00:02:21,166
This one's extra.

27
00:02:22,125 --> 00:02:23,125
Take it or leave it.

28
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:26,220
I'll take it. You've already had breakfast.

29
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:27,500
No, I haven't.

30
00:02:27,583 --> 00:02:28,663
This place isn't very good,

31
00:02:28,708 --> 00:02:29,708
so I didn't eat.

32
00:02:31,041 --> 00:02:32,041
Is this...

33
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:33,333
for me?

34
00:02:34,916 --> 00:02:35,916
There was also extra.

35
00:02:40,708 --> 00:02:42,166
This must be Auntie Meixi's cooking.

36
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:44,500
It looks delicious.

37
00:02:45,166 --> 00:02:46,166
You can have the bad one.

38
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:47,833
Thanks.

39
00:03:02,625 --> 00:03:03,625
Come on, come on.

40
00:03:04,875 --> 00:03:05,291
Pass it to me.

41
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:06,833
Here, one more.

42
00:03:08,125 --> 00:03:09,125
Let's get warmed up.

43
00:03:12,416 --> 00:03:13,500
Your dribbling isn't bad.

44
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:16,291
I practice on my own sometimes.

45
00:03:17,291 --> 00:03:18,642
Then it looks like you
mainly need to practice

46
00:03:18,666 --> 00:03:19,986
your shooting and passing skills.

47
00:03:23,458 --> 00:03:24,618
We need one more on our team.

48
00:03:25,583 --> 00:03:25,958
I'm not playing.

49
00:03:26,041 --> 00:03:26,750
Then we're not playing either.

50
00:03:26,875 --> 00:03:27,458
Then forget it.

51
00:03:27,541 --> 00:03:28,458
I've got something to do. I'm out.

52
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:29,208
How are we supposed to play with him?

53
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:30,333
Exactly.

54
00:03:30,416 --> 00:03:32,059
We might break a leg just playing with him.

55
00:03:32,083 --> 00:03:33,083
Anyone else?

56
00:03:39,833 --> 00:03:40,833
Bend your knees.

57
00:03:41,416 --> 00:03:42,416
A little lower.

58
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,500
Raise your hands.

59
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:46,708
Support it with this hand.

60
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:48,125
Guide it with this one.

61
00:03:48,541 --> 00:03:51,500
Then aim for your target.

62
00:03:52,791 --> 00:03:53,791
Then, like this,

63
00:03:53,958 --> 00:03:54,958
three fingers.

64
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:56,083
Right.

65
00:03:56,084 --> 00:03:57,375
This hand is just for support.

66
00:03:57,791 --> 00:03:58,791
Then, once you've aimed...

67
00:04:13,291 --> 00:04:14,309
Just the two of you practicing?

68
00:04:14,333 --> 00:04:15,573
Why don't we all play together?

69
00:04:16,541 --> 00:04:17,333
Yeah, come on, everyone.

70
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:18,500
Come on.

71
00:04:18,791 --> 00:04:19,875
Let's go, let's go. Hurry.

72
00:04:20,125 --> 00:04:21,125
Everyone, join in. Quick.

73
00:04:27,208 --> 00:04:28,208
Alright, serve the ball.

74
00:04:33,125 --> 00:04:34,750
Is there something wrong with this hoop?

75
00:04:35,625 --> 00:04:36,791
Don't be so dramatic.

76
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:38,309
Forget it. Let's go practice passing.

77
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:39,000
Let's not shoot here.

78
00:04:39,208 --> 00:04:40,208
Let's go, let's go.

79
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:41,333
This basketball hoop...

80
00:04:41,416 --> 00:04:42,291
Didn't someone say last time

81
00:04:42,416 --> 00:04:43,776
that the screws needed tightening?

82
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:45,250
Did no one report it?

83
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:47,416
It's fine.

84
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:48,833
I'll go get some tools.

85
00:04:49,166 --> 00:04:50,684
Isn't that the captain and
class committee's job?

86
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:51,708
Why are you going?

87
00:05:01,208 --> 00:05:01,583
What's wrong?

88
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:02,291
Are you okay?

89
00:05:02,458 --> 00:05:03,125
Try moving your ankle.

90
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:03,833
See if it's okay.

91
00:05:03,916 --> 00:05:05,676
If not, I'll take you
to the nurse's office.

92
00:05:05,916 --> 00:05:07,500
I think I'm fine.

93
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:09,166
Come on, up you go.

94
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:10,250
Alright, alright.

95
00:05:10,958 --> 00:05:11,666
Don't be so dramatic.

96
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:12,833
Everyone, be careful.

97
00:05:14,083 --> 00:05:14,500
See that?

98
00:05:14,791 --> 00:05:15,500
I was closest to you,

99
00:05:15,583 --> 00:05:16,583
but I'm perfectly fine.

100
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:18,642
You don't have to go out of your way.

101
00:05:18,666 --> 00:05:19,791
I just want to show everyone

102
00:05:19,958 --> 00:05:20,958
that you're not a jinx.

103
00:05:22,125 --> 00:05:22,666
Come on.

104
00:05:22,875 --> 00:05:23,583
Let's keep playing. Keep playing.

105
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:24,809
Play ball, play ball, play ball!

106
00:05:24,833 --> 00:05:25,416
Pass it to me.

107
00:05:25,708 --> 00:05:26,708
Here.

108
00:05:29,666 --> 00:05:30,666
Nice one!

109
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:35,416
Great shot!

110
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:36,000
Awesome!

111
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,000
Not bad.

112
00:05:38,291 --> 00:05:39,291
Let's go again.

113
00:05:42,375 --> 00:05:42,875
Give me the ball.

114
00:05:43,125 --> 00:05:43,958
Let's call it a day.

115
00:05:44,125 --> 00:05:45,184
I'm too tired to play anymore.

116
00:05:45,208 --> 00:05:46,248
Alright, let's wrap it up.

117
00:05:46,875 --> 00:05:47,458
Okay, okay.

118
00:05:47,583 --> 00:05:48,208
Let's go. Bye.

119
00:05:48,583 --> 00:05:49,583
Leaving. Bye. Let's go.

120
00:05:51,083 --> 00:05:51,458
Bian Ye.

121
00:05:52,041 --> 00:05:53,241
You're not on your game today.

122
00:05:53,625 --> 00:05:55,025
A-Ze intercepted you so many times.

123
00:05:55,583 --> 00:05:56,958
I think I pulled a thigh muscle.

124
00:05:57,875 --> 00:05:58,875
Are you okay?

125
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:00,666
It's not fatal.

126
00:06:01,250 --> 00:06:03,082
Should we go to the nurse's office?

127
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:04,083
No.

128
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:06,333
Avoiding Zhan Xu.

129
00:06:12,166 --> 00:06:13,166
Let's go.

130
00:06:27,666 --> 00:06:28,666
Sprained leg, huh.

131
00:06:28,708 --> 00:06:29,708
How did you know?

132
00:06:30,541 --> 00:06:32,166
I went to watch you practice.

133
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:34,700
You came to watch me practice?

134
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:37,750
Lie down.

135
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:13,250
It's not too bad.

136
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:14,333
It's just a mild sprain.

137
00:07:14,583 --> 00:07:15,583
Not a torn ligament.

138
00:07:16,208 --> 00:07:18,750
Plus, you've also pulled a thigh muscle.

139
00:07:21,625 --> 00:07:22,985
Let me put some ice on it for you.

140
00:07:23,083 --> 00:07:24,923
Rest for a couple of
days, and you'll be fine.

141
00:07:27,541 --> 00:07:27,958
Ow.

142
00:07:28,375 --> 00:07:29,375
Endure it.

143
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:52,208
You seem to be good at this.

144
00:08:09,166 --> 00:08:10,166
I'm a doctor.

145
00:08:11,250 --> 00:08:12,250
I mean,

146
00:08:12,541 --> 00:08:14,458
your hands are very
steady when you touch me.

147
00:08:17,666 --> 00:08:18,666
I'll go get more ice.

148
00:10:01,975 --> 00:10:03,993
[Doctor's Without Borders Treatment
Initiative, Yunnan Mountains 2020]

149
00:10:08,916 --> 00:10:09,916
Put it down.

150
00:10:12,958 --> 00:10:14,318
You were part of Doctors Without Borders?

151
00:10:15,208 --> 00:10:16,288
I never would have guessed.

152
00:10:16,541 --> 00:10:17,541
That's pretty cool.

153
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:19,708
That was a long time ago.

154
00:10:21,750 --> 00:10:23,190
Who's the other person in the photo?

155
00:10:23,791 --> 00:10:24,791
A colleague.

156
00:10:25,166 --> 00:10:26,166
Just a colleague?

157
00:10:28,916 --> 00:10:29,916
You can go now.

158
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:37,000
This thing in your ear,

159
00:10:37,541 --> 00:10:39,375
is it for listening to
music while you work?

160
00:10:43,166 --> 00:10:44,166
It's for work.

161
00:10:44,875 --> 00:10:45,995
There are some subtle sounds

162
00:10:46,583 --> 00:10:47,903
that I need to hear more clearly.

163
00:10:48,125 --> 00:10:49,125
Like what sounds?

164
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:51,250
Like...

165
00:10:51,291 --> 00:10:52,811
whether a machine is running properly.

166
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:54,875
Like...

167
00:10:55,291 --> 00:10:56,500
a patient's breathing rate.

168
00:10:58,208 --> 00:10:59,208
Like...

169
00:10:59,958 --> 00:11:01,758
the sound of your
footsteps as you leave now.

170
00:11:03,708 --> 00:11:04,908
You came to watch me practice.

171
00:11:06,125 --> 00:11:07,125
I'm the school nurse.

172
00:11:08,041 --> 00:11:09,841
Caring about the
students' physical condition

173
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:11,333
is my duty.

174
00:11:16,375 --> 00:11:17,541
Then why only watch me?

175
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:26,250
Just now,

176
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:28,083
I saw your reaction.

177
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:42,166
Is it hot in the nurse's office?

178
00:11:42,708 --> 00:11:43,708
Your hair is all wet.

179
00:11:49,583 --> 00:11:51,208
See you at the clinic at 5 p.m.

180
00:11:52,458 --> 00:11:53,818
Don't forget to do the test paper.

181
00:12:20,666 --> 00:12:21,666
Let's take a break.

182
00:12:30,375 --> 00:12:31,495
Your stamina is pretty good.

183
00:12:35,208 --> 00:12:36,568
Your coaching is pretty good, too.

184
00:12:57,835 --> 00:12:59,958
Here's your prize bottle.

185
00:13:01,791 --> 00:13:03,791
I'll come to you to claim
my prize next time, too.

186
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:12,820
You're actually not a bad player.

187
00:13:16,166 --> 00:13:17,166
A long time ago,

188
00:13:17,916 --> 00:13:19,076
my dad taught me how to play.

189
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:20,333
He was really good.

190
00:13:21,583 --> 00:13:22,583
And then?

191
00:13:26,666 --> 00:13:27,666
Then he died.

192
00:13:34,208 --> 00:13:35,208
I'm sorry.

193
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:44,541
Don't be scared on game day.

194
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:47,500
I'm not scared.

195
00:13:48,041 --> 00:13:49,401
Then stop your hands from shaking.

196
00:13:51,958 --> 00:13:52,958
They're not shaking.

197
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:55,750
Like this.

198
00:13:56,875 --> 00:13:58,195
Every time you're about to shoot,

199
00:13:58,458 --> 00:13:59,291
just imagine

200
00:13:59,458 --> 00:14:00,858
that you're holding onto something.

201
00:14:02,583 --> 00:14:03,583
Holding what?

202
00:14:04,791 --> 00:14:05,791
For example...

203
00:14:06,291 --> 00:14:07,491
wringing an enemy's neck.

204
00:14:09,583 --> 00:14:11,000
More like wringing your neck.

205
00:14:18,166 --> 00:14:19,526
Come on, I'll treat you to a meal.

206
00:14:20,666 --> 00:14:21,666
I have money.

207
00:14:22,875 --> 00:14:24,395
You have money? Then you can treat me.

208
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:26,750
Deal.

209
00:14:31,041 --> 00:14:31,750
Next up,

210
00:14:31,875 --> 00:14:34,500
we have Class 2, Grade 12,
facing last year's champions,

211
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:35,833
the Grade 11 United Team.

212
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:38,250
The pressure is on for Class 2, Grade 12.

213
00:14:38,625 --> 00:14:40,500
This is going to be a bloodbath.

214
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:44,208
Let's welcome both teams to the court!

215
00:14:44,958 --> 00:14:45,958
Victory!

216
00:14:52,166 --> 00:14:53,625
That Jinx is actually playing?

217
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:55,350
Is Grade 12 out of players or something?

218
00:14:55,416 --> 00:14:56,625
Just wait for them to lose.

219
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:57,833
Don't be cowards!

220
00:14:58,208 --> 00:15:00,041
We'll win even with the jinx on our team.

221
00:15:00,583 --> 00:15:01,875
Xu Yuan is not a Jinx.

222
00:15:02,541 --> 00:15:03,041
That's right.

223
00:15:03,208 --> 00:15:04,458
He's our class's lucky star.

224
00:15:05,791 --> 00:15:06,791
Go, Xu Yuan!

225
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:09,750
Xu Yuan! Zhan Wang!

226
00:15:09,875 --> 00:15:11,375
Class 2, Grade 12, will win!

227
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:13,333
Go!

228
00:15:17,666 --> 00:15:18,125
Offense!

229
00:15:18,583 --> 00:15:19,583
Defense!

230
00:15:19,666 --> 00:15:20,666
Nice shot!

231
00:15:21,291 --> 00:15:22,291
Awesome!

232
00:15:23,541 --> 00:15:24,750
Hurry up! Faster!

233
00:15:25,625 --> 00:15:26,625
Great shot!

234
00:16:00,583 --> 00:16:01,583
He's so cool!

235
00:16:02,166 --> 00:16:03,166
Go, go!

236
00:16:08,166 --> 00:16:09,208
You're amazing!

237
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:02,750
Xu Yuan!

238
00:17:21,416 --> 00:17:22,458
That was beautiful!

239
00:17:24,375 --> 00:17:26,875
Xu Yuan! Xu Yuan! Xu Yuan!

240
00:17:27,083 --> 00:17:29,666
Xu Yuan! Xu Yuan! Xu Yuan!

241
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:34,166
Awesome!

242
00:17:36,041 --> 00:17:37,041
We won!

243
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:40,500
We won!

244
00:17:40,583 --> 00:17:41,583
We won! We won! We won!

245
00:17:41,708 --> 00:17:42,541
We won!

246
00:17:42,625 --> 00:17:43,625
That was so cool!

247
00:17:45,125 --> 00:17:46,125
Great game.

248
00:17:47,208 --> 00:17:48,208
We won!

249
00:17:49,041 --> 00:17:49,750
We won!

250
00:17:49,875 --> 00:17:50,875
We won! We won!

251
00:18:00,208 --> 00:18:01,208
Xu Yuan!

252
00:18:01,541 --> 00:18:02,541
Come on up!

253
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:03,666
Xu Yuan, go on! Yeah!

254
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:04,541
Go, Xu Yuan!

255
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:06,266
Get on stage and get the award, Xu Yuan!

256
00:18:11,125 --> 00:18:12,125
Xu Yuan!

257
00:18:12,541 --> 00:18:13,958
The championship is ours!

258
00:18:21,958 --> 00:18:22,958
Yeah!

259
00:18:24,041 --> 00:18:25,375
Three, two, one!

260
00:18:48,125 --> 00:18:49,291
Be careful, don't fall.

261
00:18:49,375 --> 00:18:51,135
If I fall, you'll be
there to break my fall.

262
00:18:59,208 --> 00:19:00,208
Bro.

263
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,500
Let's go.

264
00:19:13,291 --> 00:19:14,291
I'll kill you!

265
00:19:15,208 --> 00:19:16,208
I told you to get lost!

266
00:19:16,541 --> 00:19:18,041
Mr. Chen said he's taking this land.

267
00:19:18,416 --> 00:19:19,776
You have to be out by the weekend.

268
00:19:19,875 --> 00:19:21,500
Are you deaf or just stupid?

269
00:19:21,916 --> 00:19:22,916
The contract says...

270
00:19:23,041 --> 00:19:25,166
It doesn't expire for another three years.

271
00:19:26,750 --> 00:19:27,750
Contract?

272
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,416
My word is the law around here.

273
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:31,125
Playing tough guy, huh?

274
00:19:31,166 --> 00:19:31,791
To hell with you!

275
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:32,833
I'll kick you to death!

276
00:19:41,083 --> 00:19:42,083
Get off!

277
00:19:42,166 --> 00:19:42,458
Mom!

278
00:19:42,458 --> 00:19:43,458
Stop fighting!

279
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,250
Another one?

280
00:19:46,291 --> 00:19:47,291
Get lost!

281
00:19:47,750 --> 00:19:49,000
Stop fighting, all of you!

282
00:19:49,416 --> 00:19:50,642
If anyone touches my son again,

283
00:19:50,666 --> 00:19:52,250
I'll die right here with you.

284
00:19:53,875 --> 00:19:55,041
She's a fucking psycho.

285
00:19:56,750 --> 00:19:57,750
Let's go.

286
00:20:03,125 --> 00:20:03,541
Mom.

287
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:04,833
It's okay. It's okay now.

288
00:20:06,791 --> 00:20:07,871
Help your mom inside first.

289
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:09,708
It's okay.

290
00:20:10,208 --> 00:20:11,208
It's okay.

291
00:20:12,916 --> 00:20:13,916
Let's go inside.

292
00:20:18,666 --> 00:20:20,958
You need to get that injury looked at.

293
00:20:25,833 --> 00:20:26,375
I'm fine.

294
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:28,020
Zhan Xu should still be at the clinic.

295
00:20:28,541 --> 00:20:29,541
Go on.

296
00:20:44,791 --> 00:20:45,851
You have such a gentle touch.

297
00:20:45,875 --> 00:20:46,875
It doesn't hurt.

298
00:20:47,875 --> 00:20:48,875
You can get up now.

299
00:20:50,208 --> 00:20:51,291
Let's have dinner tonight.

300
00:20:52,041 --> 00:20:53,841
I know a new Japanese
place that just opened.

301
00:20:53,916 --> 00:20:54,916
Sorry.

302
00:20:55,333 --> 00:20:55,916
I have plans tonight.

303
00:20:56,125 --> 00:20:57,125
Xu.

304
00:20:57,291 --> 00:20:58,291
You always turn me down.

305
00:20:58,750 --> 00:20:59,750
Are you done staring?

306
00:21:00,166 --> 00:21:01,206
If you are, you can leave.

307
00:21:05,166 --> 00:21:06,166
Bian Ye.

308
00:21:07,125 --> 00:21:08,476
What are you doing here at this hour?

309
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:09,000
What?

310
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:10,940
Did I interrupt something important?

311
00:21:11,958 --> 00:21:12,958
And this is...?

312
00:21:14,375 --> 00:21:15,375
My student.

313
00:21:16,291 --> 00:21:16,708
Right.

314
00:21:17,125 --> 00:21:17,625
A student.

315
00:21:17,958 --> 00:21:19,434
The teacher needs to tutor his student now.

316
00:21:19,458 --> 00:21:20,750
So you can leave.

317
00:21:20,958 --> 00:21:22,250
Get out. I said, get out.

318
00:21:22,583 --> 00:21:24,125
Students these days have no manners.

319
00:21:25,666 --> 00:21:26,666
Bian Ye.

320
00:21:28,208 --> 00:21:29,208
Don't be like that.

321
00:21:29,291 --> 00:21:30,291
Like what?

322
00:21:30,375 --> 00:21:31,934
And what you two were doing was so great?

323
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:33,678
He touched your hand, and you just let him.

324
00:21:34,208 --> 00:21:34,708
Zhan Xu.

325
00:21:35,125 --> 00:21:36,833
Isn't your student a little out of line?

326
00:21:39,041 --> 00:21:40,041
Say that again.

327
00:21:43,041 --> 00:21:44,041
Bian Ye.

328
00:21:44,541 --> 00:21:45,541
Let go of him.

329
00:21:53,708 --> 00:21:55,166
So this is your type now?

330
00:21:55,375 --> 00:21:56,375
A little brat.

331
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:57,083
But, Zhan Xu,

332
00:21:57,416 --> 00:21:58,696
a little "wolf pup" like this...

333
00:21:58,875 --> 00:21:59,875
is fine for a fling.

334
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:01,080
Just don't get too serious.

335
00:22:02,625 --> 00:22:03,705
I'll come back another day.

336
00:22:05,583 --> 00:22:07,343
You come back here
again, and I'll kill you.

337
00:22:08,333 --> 00:22:09,333
Bian Ye.

338
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:11,500
You've gone too far.

339
00:22:11,791 --> 00:22:12,791
I've gone too far?

340
00:22:13,250 --> 00:22:14,410
What did he mean by all that?

341
00:22:14,541 --> 00:22:15,559
What did he mean, "your type"?

342
00:22:15,583 --> 00:22:17,143
And what was that about "just a fling"?

343
00:22:19,333 --> 00:22:19,750
You should go.

344
00:22:20,041 --> 00:22:20,625
I'm not leaving.

345
00:22:20,791 --> 00:22:21,583
You need to tell me the truth.

346
00:22:21,791 --> 00:22:22,791
Do you like men?

347
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:23,833
Do you?

348
00:22:23,916 --> 00:22:24,916
With him?

349
00:22:29,125 --> 00:22:30,125
That's right.

350
00:22:30,333 --> 00:22:31,333
I like men.

351
00:22:32,208 --> 00:22:33,208
Are you happy now?

352
00:22:35,125 --> 00:22:36,458
Then why can't it be me?

353
00:22:37,583 --> 00:22:38,625
You're my student.

354
00:22:39,666 --> 00:22:40,666
And I'm your teacher.

355
00:22:41,291 --> 00:22:43,059
Do you even know what
it means to like someone?

356
00:22:43,083 --> 00:22:44,250
This is just a passing crush.

357
00:22:44,416 --> 00:22:45,416
I don't understand?

358
00:22:45,958 --> 00:22:46,958
Then you tell me.

359
00:22:47,250 --> 00:22:48,934
Who is it that makes
my heart race like this?

360
00:22:48,958 --> 00:22:50,415
Who makes me rush here to do
homework every day after class?

361
00:22:50,416 --> 00:22:51,416
Who is it?

362
00:22:51,541 --> 00:22:52,767
Who makes me want to hit
someone just for touching your hand?

363
00:22:52,791 --> 00:22:53,791
Who is it?

364
00:22:55,250 --> 00:22:56,250
Zhan Xu.

365
00:22:56,333 --> 00:22:57,333
Look at me.

366
00:22:59,166 --> 00:23:00,766
You really want to tell me
you feel nothing for me?

367
00:23:01,666 --> 00:23:02,666
Then why did you help me?

368
00:23:03,708 --> 00:23:04,748
Why did you give me money?

369
00:23:05,041 --> 00:23:06,041
Why did you fix my tooth?

370
00:23:06,958 --> 00:23:08,559
I saw you in the nurse's office that day.

371
00:23:08,583 --> 00:23:09,708
I saw how you reacted.

372
00:23:09,916 --> 00:23:10,916
Your ears turned red.

373
00:23:11,041 --> 00:23:12,142
Are you going to deny it was
because I was close to you

374
00:23:12,166 --> 00:23:13,166
that you got hard?

375
00:23:24,708 --> 00:23:25,750
You... your ear...

376
00:23:30,625 --> 00:23:31,865
Hearing damage in my right ear.

377
00:23:33,083 --> 00:23:34,083
Basically, I'm half-deaf.

378
00:23:35,583 --> 00:23:36,583
So now you know.

379
00:23:37,458 --> 00:23:39,500
I'm not just some freak who likes men.

380
00:23:40,791 --> 00:23:41,875
I'm a cripple, too.

381
00:23:42,250 --> 00:23:43,250
Are you satisfied now?

382
00:23:44,291 --> 00:23:45,291
Just go.

383
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,000
I'm not leaving.

384
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:17,500
That's them!

385
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:18,791
Run!

386
00:24:18,833 --> 00:24:19,208
Get them!

387
00:24:19,250 --> 00:24:19,833
Don't run!

388
00:24:20,083 --> 00:24:21,083
Stop!

389
00:24:21,208 --> 00:24:21,625
Don't run!

390
00:24:21,916 --> 00:24:22,916
Stop!

391
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:29,500
Where'd they go?

392
00:24:29,625 --> 00:24:30,708
This way! They're fast.

393
00:24:31,125 --> 00:24:32,125
Little punks.

394
00:24:32,166 --> 00:24:32,750
Check over there.

395
00:24:32,875 --> 00:24:33,625
I'll kill you when I catch you!

396
00:24:33,750 --> 00:24:34,750
Alright.

397
00:24:37,041 --> 00:24:38,041
Go check over there.

398
00:24:38,708 --> 00:24:39,708
Find them yet?

399
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:41,750
Where are they?

400
00:24:46,416 --> 00:24:47,416
Where are we?

401
00:24:47,791 --> 00:24:48,831
My dad's old fishing boat.

402
00:24:50,250 --> 00:24:51,250
Let's check over there.

403
00:24:51,750 --> 00:24:52,166
Let's go.

404
00:24:52,208 --> 00:24:53,208
Alright.

405
00:24:53,625 --> 00:24:54,745
There are stalls down there.

406
00:24:54,791 --> 00:24:56,031
There's no way they can escape.

407
00:24:57,125 --> 00:24:58,125
Where are they?

408
00:24:58,958 --> 00:24:59,958
They're not over here.

409
00:25:00,291 --> 00:25:01,291
Alright.

410
00:25:01,416 --> 00:25:01,791
Nothing.

411
00:25:02,416 --> 00:25:02,958
Go, go, go.

412
00:25:03,416 --> 00:25:04,458
Let's get out of here.

413
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,708
What happened to your ear?

414
00:25:13,500 --> 00:25:15,140
Is it because of the person in the photo?

415
00:25:22,166 --> 00:25:23,750
In high school, because I liked men...

416
00:25:23,958 --> 00:25:25,666
my dad slapped me more than a dozen times.

417
00:25:27,291 --> 00:25:28,571
My right eardrum was perforated.

418
00:25:37,166 --> 00:25:38,166
What happened after that?

419
00:25:38,291 --> 00:25:39,750
We ran away from home together.

420
00:25:40,333 --> 00:25:41,453
Traveled the world together.

421
00:25:42,166 --> 00:25:44,208
Provided medical aid
around the world together.

422
00:25:47,541 --> 00:25:49,416
And where is he now?

423
00:25:50,250 --> 00:25:51,250
He got married.

424
00:25:52,333 --> 00:25:54,213
His kid's starting
elementary school this year.

425
00:25:55,916 --> 00:25:57,291
Xu... I won't.

426
00:26:01,416 --> 00:26:02,416
What?

427
00:26:04,916 --> 00:26:05,916
I won't get married.

428
00:26:06,333 --> 00:26:07,333
I won't leave.

429
00:26:07,958 --> 00:26:09,583
When I commit to someone, it's forever.

430
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:16,500
You're only nineteen.

431
00:26:19,625 --> 00:26:20,625
Forever is a long time.

432
00:26:21,791 --> 00:26:22,791
So...

433
00:26:23,083 --> 00:26:24,833
I have a long time to prove it to you.

434
00:26:33,375 --> 00:26:34,375
Tell me...

435
00:26:36,375 --> 00:26:37,541
If I fell from here...

436
00:26:38,625 --> 00:26:39,625
would you save me?

437
00:26:39,875 --> 00:26:40,875
You definitely wouldn't [fall.]

438
00:26:43,083 --> 00:26:44,083
But what if?

439
00:26:50,416 --> 00:26:51,416
Really?

440
00:26:57,666 --> 00:26:58,666
Really.

441
00:27:02,666 --> 00:27:03,666
Then I'll give it a try.

442
00:27:07,416 --> 00:27:08,416
Zhan Wang!

443
00:27:10,875 --> 00:27:11,875
Zhan Wang!

444
00:27:12,583 --> 00:27:13,583
Zhan Wang!

